extension_index.description: Censor cells of a pivot table based on the values of a tests

extension_detail_info.Name: SPSSINC CENSOR TABLES
extension_detail_info.Summary: Censor cells of a pivot table based on the values of a test statistic
extension_detail_info.Description: Use this command to blank out or otherwise obscure cells in the most recent pivot table of a selected type based on the value of a specified statistic in the table. For example, you can blank out cell statistics based on small counts or blank out insignificant correlations in a correlation matrix.
extension_detail_info.Author: IBM SPSS

extension_index.description: Compare two open datasets.

extension_detail_info.Name: SPSSINC COMPARE DATASETS
extension_detail_info.Summary: Compare two open datasets.
extension_detail_info.Description: This procedure compares two open datasets. You can specify whether the comparison includes the case data, the variable properties or both.
extension_detail_info.Author: IBM SPSS

extension_index.description: Create a set of dummy variables representing the values of on

extension_detail_info.Name: SPSSINC CREATE DUMMIES
extension_detail_info.Summary: Create a set of dummy variables representing the values of one or more variables and interaction terms
extension_detail_info.Description: This procedure creates a set of 0-1 dummy variables representing the distinct values of one or more variables. It can also create dummies for two- and three-way interaction terms.  It is useful, for example, in converting categorical variables into a set of variables appropriate for use in the Regression procedure. It can optionally create  macro variables representing sets of dummies.
extension_detail_info.Author: JKP, IBM SPSS

extension_index.description: Open an SPSS, Excel, SAS, or Stata dataset from a web url.

extension_detail_info.Name: SPSSINC GETURI DATA
extension_detail_info.Summary: Open an SPSS, Excel, SAS, or Stata dataset from a web url.
extension_detail_info.Description: This command takes a URL as input and downloads and opens a data file.  It can be used to download and save files of other types, but these will not be opened.
extension_detail_info.Author: JKP, IBM SPSS

extension_index.description: Calculate correlations between nominal, ordinal, and scale va

extension_detail_info.Name: SPSSINC HETCOR
extension_detail_info.Summary: Calculate correlations between nominal, ordinal, and scale variables.
extension_detail_info.Description: This procedure calculates correlations between nominal, ordinal, and scale variables, accounting for the measurement levels of the variables. The resulting heterogeneous correlation matrix consists of Pearson product-moment correlations between scale variables, polyserial correlations between scale and categorical variables, and polychoric correlations between categorical variables. The procedure uses the hetcor function from the R polycor package.
extension_detail_info.Author: IBM SPSS

extension_index.description: Merge the contents of one pivot table in the Viewer into anot

extension_detail_info.Name: SPSSINC MERGE TABLES
extension_detail_info.Summary: Merge the contents of one pivot table in the Viewer into another.
extension_detail_info.Description: This procedure combines cell values from one table with values in another table. The most common usage is to combine proportion or means test tables from Custom Tables with the main table, but many other kinds of merges are possible.
extension_detail_info.Author: IBM SPSS

extension_index.description: Modify the appearance of pivot tables.

extension_detail_info.Name: SPSSINC MODIFY TABLES
extension_detail_info.Summary: Modify the appearance of pivot tables.
extension_detail_info.Description: This procedure allows you to modify the appearance of data cells and row and column labels. You can modify text style, text color or background color. You can also set column widths or the width of row labels and you can hide specified rows or columns.
extension_detail_info.Author: IBM SPSS

extension_index.description: Apply a file of syntax to a set of data files

extension_detail_info.Name: SPSSINC PROCESS FILES
extension_detail_info.Summary: Apply a file of syntax to a set of data files
extension_detail_info.Description: This procedure applies a file of syntax to each of a group of selected files. It defines file handles and macros for use in the syntax file, and provides various options for handling Viewer and data output.
extension_detail_info.Author: JKP, IBM SPSS

extension_index.description: Estimate a regression with fractional polynomials for the scale variables

extension_detail_info.Name: SPSSINC MFP GLM
extension_detail_info.Summary: Estimate a regression with fractional polynomials for the scale variables
extension_detail_info.Description: This procedure estimates fractional polynomial models with a variety of link functions.  Controls are available to limit the degree of the polynomial
extension_detail_info.Author: JKP, IBM SPSS

extension_index.description: Modify output titles and other aspects of objects in the View

extension_detail_info.Name: SPSSINC MODIFY OUTPUT
extension_detail_info.Summary: Modify output titles and other aspects of objects in the Viewer
extension_detail_info.Description: This procedure allows you to modify the text of specified items in the outline pane of the Viewer as well as the titles (such as pivot table titles) or text (such as for title items) of the associated items. Replacement text can contain html or rtf formatting notation. Optionally, you can hide specified items and you can insert page breaks before specified title items.  Using included custom functions, selected items can be exported, and there is extra page break functionality.
extension_detail_info.Author: IBM SPSS

extension_index.description: Search the cases in a set of SPSS SAV files

extension_detail_info.Name: SPSSINC PROCESS FILES_SEARCH
extension_detail_info.Summary: Search the cases in a set of SPSS SAV files
extension_detail_info.Description: This procedure provides a way to search through the cases in a collection of similarly structured data files and display information from those matching the search criteria. You specify the files to search, the case selection criterion, and the variables to display for the selected cases. This bundle requires the SPSSINC PROCESS FILES extension.
extension_detail_info.Author: JKP IBM SPSS

extension_index.description: Extension command to run arbitrary Python programs without tu

extension_detail_info.Name: SPSSINC PROGRAM
extension_detail_info.Summary: Extension command to run arbitrary Python programs without turning them into extension commands
extension_detail_info.Description: This extension command allows you to run Python programs as if they were extension commands but without actually making them into such.  The primary benefit is that it is easy to pass parameters to programs this way.
extension_detail_info.Author: JKP, IBM SPSS

extension_index.description: Two variable or two group Q-Q plot

extension_detail_info.Name: SPSSINC QQPLOT2
extension_detail_info.Summary: Two variable or two group Q-Q plot
extension_detail_info.Description: The standard Q-Q plot in Statistics plots a variable against a theoretical distribution.  This package produces a Q-Q plot of one variable against another one or a plot of a variable's distribution in one group against the distribution in another group.
extension_detail_info.Author: JKP, IBM SPSS

extension_index.description: Estimate one or more conditional quantiles for a linear model.

extension_detail_info.Name: SPSSINC QUANTREG
extension_detail_info.Summary: Estimate one or more conditional quantiles for a linear model.
extension_detail_info.Description: This procedure estimates one or more conditional quantiles (0 <= q <= 1) for a linear model, using the rq function from the R quantreg package. In contrast, ordinary regression estimates the conditional mean. The procedure allows you to choose the estimation algorithm as well as the method for estimating the standard error. You can save both the residuals from the regression and the estimated coefficients.
extension_detail_info.Author: IBM SPSS

extension_index.description: Calculate weights to control totals in up to ten dimensions by rim weighting, i.e. raking

extension_detail_info.Name: SPSSINC_RAKE
extension_detail_info.Summary: Calculate weights to control totals in up to ten dimensions by rim weighting, i.e. raking
extension_detail_info.Description: This procedure calculates a weight so that the case count will match specified control totals in one to ten dimensions.  This procedure requires the Advanced Statistics option.  Version 2.4 improves the weight calculations when there is an input weight.
extension_detail_info.Author: JKP, IBM SPSS

extension_index.description: Estimate random forest

extension_detail_info.Name: SPSSINC RANFOR
extension_detail_info.Summary: Estimate random forest
extension_detail_info.Description: This procedure builds random forests of classification or regression trees.  It also supports unsupervised mode, in which case proximities are calculated.  The companion procedure SPSSINC RANPRED calculates predictions for new data using the forest built by this procedure.  Note: this version is a major rewrite of the older SPSSINC RANFOR procedure and  no longer requires the Python plugin.
extension_detail_info.Author: JKP, IBM SPSS

extension_index.description: Compute predicted values for new data using forests from SPSS

extension_detail_info.Name: SPSSINC RANPRED
extension_detail_info.Summary: Compute predicted values for new data using forests from SPSSINC RANFOR
extension_detail_info.Description: This procedure uses a forest produced by the SPSSINC RANFOR extension command to compute predicted values for new data.  It is a complete rewrite of the older extension command and no longer requires the Python plugin.
extension_detail_info.Author: JKP, IBM SPSS

extension_index.description: Estimate a Rasch model for item response data.

extension_detail_info.Name: SPSSINC RASCH
extension_detail_info.Summary: Estimate a Rasch model for item response data.
extension_detail_info.Description: This procedure estimates the parameters of the Rasch model for item response data, using the rasch function from the R ltm package.
extension_detail_info.Author: IBM SPSS

extension_index.description: Estimate a linear regression model by robust regression, using an M estimator

extension_detail_info.Name: SPSSINC ROBUST REGR
extension_detail_info.Summary: Estimate a linear regression model by robust regression, using an M estimator.
extension_detail_info.Description: This procedure estimates a linear regression model, robustly, using an M estimator. It uses the rlm function from the R MASS package. The procedure allows you to save both the residuals from the regression and the estimated coefficients.
extension_detail_info.Author: IBM SPSS

extension_index.description: Define a macro listing variables selected according to variable dictionary properties

extension_detail_info.Name: SPSSINC SELECT VARIABLES
extension_detail_info.Summary: Define a macro listing variables selected according to variable dictionary properties
extension_detail_info.Description: This package provides a way to select variables based on a combination of criteria.  The criteria can include names, patterns in the names, variable type, measurement level, role, and custom attributes.  Using this method, jobs can be generalized so that they do not require hard-wired variable names.
extension_detail_info.Author: JKP, IBM SPSS

extension_index.description: Estimate a linear model and perform a heteroscedasticity test.

extension_detail_info.Name: SPSSINC BREUSCH PAGAN
extension_detail_info.Summary: Estimate a linear model and perform a heteroscedasticity test.
extension_detail_info.Description: This procedure estimates a linear model and performs the Breusch-Pagan heteroscedasticity test, using the ncv.test function from the R car package. The null hypothesis is constant error variance. You can specify whether the alternative is that the variance is a function of the dependent variable or a function of a specified set of predictors. The procedure allows you to save both the residuals from the regression and the estimated coefficients.
extension_detail_info.Author: IBM SPSS

extension_index.description: Split a dataset into separate files according to splitting va

extension_detail_info.Name: SPSSINC SPLIT DATASET
extension_detail_info.Summary: Split a dataset into separate files according to splitting variables
extension_detail_info.Description: This procedure partitions a dataset into a set of sav files according to the values of one or more splitting variables.  Used with SPSSINC PROCESS FILES, it provides a generalization of the built-in SPLIT FILES mechanism.
extension_detail_info.Author: JKP, IBM SPSS

extension_index.description: Calculate a t test from the N's, means, and standard deviations rather than the case data

extension_detail_info.Name: SPSSINC SUMMARY TTEST
extension_detail_info.Summary: Calculate a t test from sample summary information
extension_detail_info.Description: This procedure calculates a t test from just the summary information of the two samples: means, standard deviations, and case counts.
extension_detail_info.Author: JKP, IBM SPSS

extension_index.description: Estimate a regression model whose dependent variable has a fi

extension_detail_info.Name: SPSSINC TOBIT REGR
extension_detail_info.Summary: Estimate a regression model whose dependent variable has a fixed lower bound, upper bound, or both.
extension_detail_info.Description: This procedure estimates a regression model where the dependent variable has a fixed lower bound, upper bound, or both. It can be thought of as a combination of a probit model with a linear regression model. You can specify the distribution assumed for the dependent variable, and you can save the residuals from the regression as well as the estimated coefficients. The procedure uses the tobit function from the R AER package.
extension_detail_info.Author: IBM SPSS

extension_index.description: Apply a Python function to case data.

extension_detail_info.Name: SPSSINC TRANS
extension_detail_info.Summary: Apply a Python function to case data.
extension_detail_info.Description: This procedure applies a Python function to the cases in the active dataset and saves the results to one or more new or existing variables. This allows you to apply Python functions to your case data, much like you do with built-in functions such as those available with the COMPUTE command.
extension_detail_info.Author: JKP, IBM SPSS

extension_index.description: Framework for translating Viewer output

extension_detail_info.Name: SPSSINC TRANSLATE OUTPUT
extension_detail_info.Summary: Framework for translating Viewer output
extension_detail_info.Description: This package provides a mechanism for translating Viewer output based on a set of supplementary files containing translations.  See the included file translator.doc for instructions.
extension_detail_info.Author: JKP, IBM SPSS

extension_index.description: Adjust widths of string variables across files

extension_detail_info.Name: STATS ADJUST WIDTHS
extension_detail_info.Summary: Adjust widths of string variables across files
extension_detail_info.Description: This command synchronizes the widths of selected string variables across a set of files or datasets. This is mainly useful when combining files with MATCH  or ADD.
extension_detail_info.Author: JKP, IBM

extension_index.description: Create a bagplot or a matrix of bagplots

extension_detail_info.Name: STATS BAGPLOT
extension_detail_info.Summary: Create a bagplot or a matrix of bagplots
extension_detail_info.Description: This procedure creates bagplots.  A bagplot is a two-dimensional generalization of a boxplot.  With more than two variables, a matrix of bagplots is created.
extension_detail_info.Author: JKP, IBM SPSS

extension_index.description: Benchmark Statistics Jobs

extension_detail_info.Name: STATS BENCHMRK
extension_detail_info.Summary: Benchmark Statistics Jobs
extension_detail_info.Description: This command runs one or two syntax files repeatedly and records various statistics on time, memory, and i/o resource usage by the computer processes associated with Statistics.  It requires the Python Extensions for Windows.
extension_detail_info.Author: JKP, IBM SPSS

extension_index.description: Calculate canonical correlations

extension_detail_info.Name: STATS CANCORR
extension_detail_info.Summary: Calculate canonical correlations
extension_detail_info.Description: This procedures computes canonical correlations for two sets of variables.  It can create scores, and it can produce a syntax file that can be used to score other datasets with the same variable names.
extension_detail_info.Author: JKP, IBM SPSS

extension_index.description: Compute the Cartesian product of two sets of variables

extension_detail_info.Name: STATS CARTPROD
extension_detail_info.Summary: Compute the Cartesian product of two sets of variables
extension_detail_info.Description: This command takes two sets of variables either from the active dataset or the active dataset plus one other dataset and creates a new data file containing the Cartesian product of the variables.
extension_detail_info.Author: JKP, IBM SPSS

extension_index.description: Create a macro or multiple dichotomy set with a specified var

extension_detail_info.Name: STATS CATEGORY ORDER
extension_detail_info.Summary: Create a macro or multiple dichotomy set with a specified variable order
extension_detail_info.Description: This procedure takes a list of ordinary variables or multiple dichotomy sets.  For ordinary variables, it creates a macro listing the variables in sorted order of the count.  This macro can be used in the CTABLES CATEGORIES subcommand to control the order in the table.  Unlike CTABLES, it can move special values out of the sort order.  For multiple dichotomy sets, it creates a new set with the categories similarly reordered.
extension_detail_info.Author: JKP, IBM SPSS

extension_index.description: compute silhouette measure for cluster analysis

extension_detail_info.Name: STATS CLUS SIL
extension_detail_info.Summary: compute silhouette measure for cluster analysis
extension_detail_info.Description: This procedure computes and optionally plots silhouette measures useful in assessing the quality of a cluster analysis.  It provides several different dissimilarity measures and plots that work with the output from a cluster analysis procedure
extension_detail_info.Author: JKP, IBM SPSS

extension_index.description: Competing risk survival regression

extension_detail_info.Name: STATS COMPRISK
extension_detail_info.Summary: Competing risk survival regression
extension_detail_info.Description: This procedure estimates the   competing risks survival regression model.  This model allows for multiple   competing causes for the failure event.  These could, for example, be multiple   health conditions or multiple part failures in a mechanical or electrical device.
extension_detail_info.Author: JKP, IBM SPSS

extension_index.description: Cox (proportional hazards) regression

extension_detail_info.Name: STATS COXREGR
extension_detail_info.Summary: Cox (proportional hazards) regression
extension_detail_info.Description: This procedure calculates Cox regession.  It has some features not available in the Statistics COXREG procedure.  It supports left and/or right censoring via a counting process model.  Time dependent variables are supported via either a formula or multiple observations per subject.
extension_detail_info.Author: JKP, IBM SPSS

extension_index.description: Define date structure based on dataset values

extension_detail_info.Name: STATS_DATA_DATE
extension_detail_info.Summary: Define date structure based on dataset values
extension_detail_info.Description: This procedure defines the date structure of the dataset based on the first value of an SPSS date variable
extension_detail_info.Author: JKP, IBM SPSS

extension_index.description: Combine several DATASET commands into one

extension_detail_info.Name: STATS DATASET
extension_detail_info.Summary: Combine several DATASET commands into one
extension_detail_info.Description: This command combines the functions of DATASET NAME, DATASET ACTIVATE, DATASET CLOSE, and DATASET DISPLAY into a single command.  It also allow you to close all the datasets except for a specified list without having to list every dataset individually.
extension_detail_info.Author: JKP, IBM SPSS

extension_index.description: Prediction based on density-based clustering

extension_detail_info.Name: STATS_DBPRED
extension_detail_info.Summary: Prediction based on density-based clustering
extension_detail_info.Description: This procedure uses the results of the companion procedure, STATS_DBSCAN, to predict cluster values for new cases.
extension_detail_info.Author: JKP, IBM SPSS

extension_index.description: Density-based clustering

extension_detail_info.Name: STATS_DBSCAN
extension_detail_info.Summary: Density-based clustering
extension_detail_info.Description: This procedure calculates density-based clusters allowing for noise.  The companion procedure, STATS_DBPRED, can be used to predict values for new cases.
extension_detail_info.Author: JKP, IBM SPSS

extension_index.description: Disaggregate a time series into a series at a higher frequency

extension_detail_info.Name: STATS DISAGG
extension_detail_info.Summary: Disaggregate a time series into a series at a higher frequency
extension_detail_info.Description: This command creates a new dataset containing a time series at a higher frequency than the original.  It can use higher frequency indicator variables with which the low frequency is correlated to distribute the values or distribute less accurately without such indicators.  Several methods are supported.
extension_detail_info.Author: JKP, IBM SPSS

extension_index.description: Fit probability distributions

extension_detail_info.Name: STATS DISTFIT
extension_detail_info.Summary: Fit probability distributions
extension_detail_info.Description: This package fits one or more selected probability distributions to a collection of variables.  The output includes the fit parameters, a goodness-of-fit test, and, optionally, Q-Q plots.
extension_detail_info.Author: JKP, IBM SPSS

extension_index.description: Estimate system of linear equations

extension_detail_info.Name: STATS EQNSYSTEM
extension_detail_info.Summary: Estimate system of linear equations
extension_detail_info.Description: This procedure estimates a system of linear equations by 3SLS, 2SLS, SUR, or OLS.  The dialog box handles only two equations, but an unlimited number can be used in syntax.
extension_detail_info.Author: JKP, IBM SPSS

extension_index.description: Create file handle in location of a searched for file

extension_detail_info.Name: STATS FIND FILE
extension_detail_info.Summary: Create file handle in location of a searched for file
extension_detail_info.Description: By using this command, you can create jobs that do not have to know exactly where their input data and syntax files reside.  The command creates a file handle pointing to the location where a file is found following a specified search strategy.  The strategy consists of a list of locations to look in.  This can be a list of folders and/or a list of environment variables whose values are lists of folders.
extension_detail_info.Author: JKP, IBM SPSS

extension_index.description: Firth logistic regression

extension_detail_info.Name: STATS FIRTHLOG
extension_detail_info.Summary: Firth logistic regression
extension_detail_info.Description: This procedure calculates the Firth logistic regression model, which can address the separation issues that can arise in standard logistic regression.
extension_detail_info.Author: JKP, IBM SPSS

extension_index.description: GARCH models

extension_detail_info.Name: STATS GARCH
extension_detail_info.Summary: GARCH models
extension_detail_info.Description: This procedure calculates a variety of univariate GARCH models.  The models can be used for forecasting.
extension_detail_info.Author: JKP, IBM SPSS

extension_index.description: Estimate generalized boosted regression models

extension_detail_info.Name: STATS GBM
extension_detail_info.Summary: Estimate generalized boosted regression models
extension_detail_info.Description: This procedure produces a set (ensemble) of individually weak regression models that in the aggregate can predict a dependent variable more accurately than standard models.  It covers distributions from gaussian to Bernoulli -a total of ten distributions.  It is based on the R gbm package which follows the Friedman gradient boosting method.  This package performs the estimation.  The accompanying package, STATS GBMPRED, is used to calculate predictions based on the results of this procedure.
extension_detail_info.Author: JKP, IBM

extension_index.description: Calculate predictions from generalized boosted regression mod

extension_detail_info.Name: STATS GBMPRED
extension_detail_info.Summary: Calculate predictions from generalized boosted regression models created with STATS GBM
extension_detail_info.Description: This package is a companion to the STATS GBM package, which creates generalized boosted regression models.  The package reads the results of STATS GBM and creates a new dataset of predictions for new data.  It is based on the R gbm package also used by STATS GBM
extension_detail_info.Author: JKP, IBM SPSS

extension_index.description: Get information about R workspace contents and create SPSS da

extension_detail_info.Name: STATS GET R
extension_detail_info.Summary: Get information about R workspace contents and create SPSS datasets
extension_detail_info.Description: This command can display information about a R workspace file or dataset and can convert a data frame to a Statistics dataset.  It can also display a list of all datasets associated with the installed R packages.
extension_detail_info.Author: JKP, IBM SPSS

extension_index.description: Read a file in Triple-S format

extension_detail_info.Name: STATS GET TRIPLES
extension_detail_info.Summary: Read a file in Triple-S format
extension_detail_info.Description: Triple-S is an open standard for data files, primarily surveys.  This command reads a fixed-format or csv file conforming to this standard.  It can also generate and save a syntax file for reading the data.
extension_detail_info.Author: JKP, IBM SPSS

extension_index.description: Fit graded response models to ordinal data

extension_detail_info.Name: STATS_GRM
extension_detail_info.Summary: Fit graded response models to ordinal data
extension_detail_info.Description: Fits the grm function from the R ltm package to graded response data
extension_detail_info.Author: Alex Reutter, IBM SPSS

extension_index.description: Estimate censored/truncated regression or switching regression

extension_detail_info.Name: STATS_HECKMAN_REGR
extension_detail_info.Summary: Estimate censored/truncated regression or switching regression
extension_detail_info.Description: This package estimates Heckman two-step regression models for a censored or truncated dependent variable.  It can also estimate switching regressions. Estimation methods include maximum likelihood and two step.
extension_detail_info.Author: JKP, IBM SPSS

extension_index.description: Execute blocks of code conditionally

extension_detail_info.Name: STATS IF
extension_detail_info.Summary: Execute blocks of code conditionally
extension_detail_info.Description: This command accepts a list of logical conditions and executes the associated block of code for the first condition that is true.  Conditions are written as Python expressions in which the values are from previously executed Python code or Python apis.
extension_detail_info.Author: JKP, IBM SPSS

extension_index.description: Various inequality measures for a variable distribution

extension_detail_info.Name: STATS INEQUALITY
extension_detail_info.Summary: Various inequality measures for a variable distribution
extension_detail_info.Description: This command computes up to seven inequality measures, including the Gini coefficient, for a variable.  Confidence intervals are available for Gini coefficients.  Split files are supported, making group comparisons easy.
extension_detail_info.Author: JKP, IBM SPSS

extension_index.description: Fit three parameter item response models

extension_detail_info.Name: STATS_IRM
extension_detail_info.Summary: Fit three parameter item response models
extension_detail_info.Description: Executes the tpm function from the R ltm package.  The variable list specifies the items.  It is assumed that the values of these variables is 0,1.
extension_detail_info.Author: Alex Reutter, IBM SPSS

extension_index.description: Fit kernel-smoothed distributions

extension_detail_info.Name: STATS KERNEL DENSITY
extension_detail_info.Summary: Fit kernel-smoothed distributions
extension_detail_info.Description: This procedure calculates kernel-smoothed densities.  It can save the densities as datasets and plot them.  The calculations are similar to the smooths available via GPL.
extension_detail_info.Author: JKP, IBM SPSS

extension_index.description: Latent Class Analysis

extension_detail_info.Name: STATS LATENT CLASS
extension_detail_info.Summary: Latent Class Analysis
extension_detail_info.Description: Extension command for latent class analysis including latent class regression using the R poLCA package by Drew Linzer and Jeffrey Lewis
extension_detail_info.Author: JKP, IBM SPSS

extension_index.description: Fit a loess curve to a model

extension_detail_info.Name: STATS LOESS
extension_detail_info.Summary: Fit a loess curve to a model
extension_detail_info.Description: This procedure fits a loess curve to a model with one to four independent variables and creates a new dataset.  The dataset contains the predicted values for the estimation data or new data as well as the prediction input data.
extension_detail_info.Author: JKP, IBM SPSS

extension_index.description: Solve linear and integer programming problems

extension_detail_info.Name: STATS_LP
extension_detail_info.Summary: Solve linear and integer programming problems
extension_detail_info.Description: This package solves linear and integer programming problems and mixed problems.  Bounds can be imposed on the objective function variables.  It can even be used to solve systems of linear equations by using all equality constraints.
extension_detail_info.Author: JKP, IBM SPSS

extension_index.description: Convert a multiple category set to a multiple dichotomy set.

extension_detail_info.Name: STATS MCSET CONVERT
extension_detail_info.Summary: Convert a multiple category set to a multiple dichotomy set
extension_detail_info.Description: This procedure converts a multiple category set into a multiple dichotomy set representing the same information.  This can be useful in conjunction with the STATS CATEGORY ORDER extension command or in order to tabulate individual values or to create dummy variables for use in procedures such as regression.
extension_detail_info.Author: JKP, IBM SPSS

extension_index.description: Open a project

extension_detail_info.Name: STATS OPEN PROJECT
extension_detail_info.Summary: Open a project
extension_detail_info.Description: This command opens a project.  A project consists of Statistics syntax, files of type syntax and output, and other projects.  Any syntax is run, and listed files are opened.  A project can be set to open automatically when Statistics starts.
extension_detail_info.Author: JKP, IBM SPSS

extension_index.description: Construct optimal bins for categorical or continuous target

extension_detail_info.Name: STATS OPTBINEX
extension_detail_info.Summary: Construct optimal bins for categorical or continuous target
extension_detail_info.Description: This command uses the TREE CHAID algorithm on a categorical or continuous target to group categories or ranges of predictor values that have statistically indistinguishable effects on the target.  It can carry out the transformations and save that syntax for future use.  It also provides value labels for the new variables.  Predictor variables are analyzed one at a time.  The results are similar to those from OPTIMAL BINNING for continuous variables and ADP, but has the advantage of exposing the transformations and providing labels.  The command requires the Decision Trees option, because it uses the TREE procedure.
extension_detail_info.Author: JKP, IBM SPSS

extension_index.description: Generate an optimal design

extension_detail_info.Name: STATS OPTIMAL DESIGNMC
extension_detail_info.Summary: Generate an optimal design
extension_detail_info.Description: This procedure generates an optimal experimental design dataset using Monte Carlo methods and the Federov algorithm.
extension_detail_info.Author: JKP, IBM SPSS

extension_index.description: Set Viewer page attributes and setup via syntax

extension_detail_info.Name: STATS OUTPUT ATTRS
extension_detail_info.Summary: Set Viewer page attributes and setup via syntax
extension_detail_info.Description: This command sets various attributes that apply to printing and exporting of the Viewer contents. These include header and footer text, page margins and orientation, starting page number, and spacing between output objects. All of these attributes can be set interactively using the Page Attributes and Page Setup dialogs on the Viewer File menu.  This dialog can generate syntax to allow these attributes to be set in batch or production jobs.
extension_detail_info.Author: JKP, IBM SPSS

extension_index.description: Calculate p-values adjusted for multiple testing

extension_detail_info.Name: STATS PADJUST
extension_detail_info.Summary: Calculate p-values adjusted for multiple testing
extension_detail_info.Description: This command calculates adjusted p values that account for multiple testing.  It includes false discovery rate and family-wise error rate adjustments.  The input is a dataset of p values or a list of values given in the command.
extension_detail_info.Author: JKP, IBM SPSS

extension_index.description: Display summary information for PMML files

extension_detail_info.Name: STATS PMML DISPLAY
extension_detail_info.Summary: Display summary information for PMML files
extension_detail_info.Description: This command reads a set of PMML files and for each one displays a summary of the model it contains.
extension_detail_info.Author: JKP, IBM SPSS

extension_index.description: Linear models for dependent variables that are proportions

extension_detail_info.Name: STATS PROPOR REGR
extension_detail_info.Summary: Linear models for dependent variables that are proportions
extension_detail_info.Description: This procedure estimates a  linear model with a link function for equations where the dependent variable is a proportion with a beta distribution.  Mean and precision parameters of the distribution are estimated.  Residuals and fitted values can be saved.  The estimated model can be saved and used for predictions on new data with the STATS PROPOR REGRPRED extension command.
extension_detail_info.Author: JKP, IBM SPSS

extension_index.description: Calculate predicted values for proportional regression models

extension_detail_info.Name: STATS PROPOR REGRPRED
extension_detail_info.Summary: Calculate predicted values for proportional regression models
extension_detail_info.Description: This procedure takes a model estimated by the STATS PROPOR REGR extension command and uses it to calculate predicted values of various types for new data.
extension_detail_info.Author: JKP, IBM SPSS

extension_index.description: Regression Discontinuity Analysis

extension_detail_info.Name: STATS RDD
extension_detail_info.Summary: Regression Discontinuity Analysis
extension_detail_info.Description: This command estimates the effects of a treatment on an output in a nonexperimental context.  The treatment is applied based on whether an observed assignment variable (also known as a running variable) exceeds a known threshold.
extension_detail_info.Author: JKP, IBM SPSS

extension_index.description: Plots useful in assessing regression relationships

extension_detail_info.Name: STATS REGRESS PLOT
extension_detail_info.Summary: Plots useful in assessing regression relationships
extension_detail_info.Description: This package provides plots that may be useful in assessing relationships between variables.  Scatterplots or categorical plots are produced depending on the variable measurement levels.  Options include fit lines, binning, paneling, and bordered boxplots on scatters.
extension_detail_info.Author: JKP, IBM SPSS

extension_index.description: Relative importance measures for regression

extension_detail_info.Name: STATS RELIMP
extension_detail_info.Summary: Relative importance measures for regression
extension_detail_info.Description: This package provides various relative importance measures for regression explanatory variables and shows how regression coefficients vary as the model size changes.
extension_detail_info.Author: JKP, IBM SPSS

extension_index.description: Play Selected Sound

extension_detail_info.Name: STATS SOUND
extension_detail_info.Summary: Play Selected Sound
extension_detail_info.Description: This command, which is only available for Microsoft Windows, plays the specified sound or sound file.  It can be useful when a long running job needs an audible notification at a selected point.  The specific sound definitions are defined in the Windows Control Panel
extension_detail_info.Author: JKP, IBM SPSS

extension_index.description: Test for structural change in regresion models with ordered c

extension_detail_info.Name: STATS STRUC CHANGE
extension_detail_info.Summary: Test for structural change in regresion models with ordered cases
extension_detail_info.Description: This package calculates a linear model for specified variables and provides plots and test statistics for structural change.  Cases should be time series data or ordered by another variable.
extension_detail_info.Author: JKP, IBM SPSS

extension_index.description: Graphically compare the distributions of a set of variables a

extension_detail_info.Name: STATS SUBGROUP PLOTS
extension_detail_info.Summary: Graphically compare the distributions of a set of variables across a partition of the data
extension_detail_info.Description: This procedure produces a set of small plots for specified variables for each subgroup in a dataset.  Each plot shows the distribution of a variable in that subgroup overlaid on the distribution of the entire dataset.  The type of plot depends on the measurement level of the variable.
extension_detail_info.Author: JKP, IBM SPSS

extension_index.description: Parametric Survival Regression

extension_detail_info.Name: STATS SURVREG
extension_detail_info.Summary: Parametric Survival Regression
extension_detail_info.Description: This procedure calculates survival regressions for left, right, interval, or counting censoring and for Weibull, exponential, gaussian, logistic, and other distributions.  Residuals and predicted values of various types can be saved as datasets.  The package can do Tobit regression as a special case.
extension_detail_info.Author: JKP, IBM SPSS

extension_index.description: Support Vector Machine

extension_detail_info.Name: STATS SVM
extension_detail_info.Summary: Support Vector Machine
extension_detail_info.Description: Construct a support vector machine and use it for predictions.  The procedure supports linear or nonlinear classifiers and regression with four choices of kernels.  A grid search over the parameter space can be carried out.
extension_detail_info.Author: JKP, IBM SPSS

extension_index.description: Calculate with pivot table cells

extension_detail_info.Name: STATS_TABLE_CALC
extension_detail_info.Summary: Calculate with pivot table cells
extension_detail_info.Description: This command calculates values using cells in a pivot table and saves the result in existing or new columns and rows of the table.
extension_detail_info.Author: JKP, IBM SPSS

extension_index.description: Perform cointegration and stationarity tests for time series

extension_detail_info.Name: STATS TSTESTS
extension_detail_info.Summary: Perform cointegration and stationarity tests for time series data
extension_detail_info.Description: This procedure performs one or more of the Phillips-Ouliaris cointegration test, the Phillips-Perron unit root test, the augmented Dickey-Fuller test, and the Kwiatkowski-Phillips_Schmidt-Shinn test.
extension_detail_info.Author: JKP, IBM SPSS

extension_index.description: Create value labels for variables from data

extension_detail_info.Name: STATS VALLBLS FROMDATA
extension_detail_info.Summary: Create value labels for variables from data
extension_detail_info.Description: This command creates value labels for selected variables using other variables as the source of the labels.  The variables to label and the label source variables can be listed or selected using patterns in the names.  The labels can be applied directly by this command, but the VALUE LABEL syntax can also be written to a file.
extension_detail_info.Author: JKP, IBM SPSS

extension_index.description: Create Weibull probability plot for failure data

extension_detail_info.Name: STATS WEIBULL PLOT
extension_detail_info.Summary: Create Weibull probability plot for failure data
extension_detail_info.Description: This procedure creates a Weibull probability plot for data on item failures and suspensions.  It requires the Graphboard template weibull.viztemplate, which must be installed separately (use Graphics >Graphboard Template Chooser> Manage) and at least Statistics version 20 plus Fixpack1.  It can be used with version 19 if the hotfix for the cloglog scale is installed
extension_detail_info.Author: JKP, IBM SPSS, JC, IBM SPSS

extension_index.description: Estimate and predict a zero-inflated count model

extension_detail_info.Name: STATS ZEROINFL
extension_detail_info.Summary: Estimate and predict a zero-inflated count model
extension_detail_info.Description: This procedure estimates mixture models consisting of a Poisson or negative binomial count model and a point mass at zero.  The predictors can be different for the two models.  The estimated model can be saved and used for predictions on new data.
extension_detail_info.Author: JKP, IBM SPSS

extension_index.description: Create a text block in the Viewer, optionally with formatted

extension_detail_info.Name: TEXT
extension_detail_info.Summary: Create a text block in the Viewer, optionally with formatted text
extension_detail_info.Description: The command provides a way in syntax to create a block of text for comments and annotations of the output.  The output can be plain text, html, or rtf
extension_detail_info.Author: JKP, IBM SPSS

extension_index.description: Configural Frequency Analysis (after von Eye and Krauth)

extension_detail_info.Name: CFA
extension_detail_info.Summary: Configural Frequency Analysis (after von Eye and Krauth)
extension_detail_info.Description: Dialog to perform a Configural Frequency Analysis. This is a method to test if there are significantly more (or less) cell frequencies in a cross table than expected. Tests available: z-values (standardized residuals) and asymptotic binomial. The dialog can handle sampling and structural zeros.
extension_detail_info.Author: Dr. Hans Grüner (http://gruener.userpage.fu-berlin.de)
extension_detail_info.Categories: binomial, dialog, graphics, plots, residuals, statistics, tables, tests, z-values

extension_index.description: Column proportions test (z-test)

extension_detail_info.Name: ColPropTest
extension_detail_info.Summary: Column proportions test (z-test)
extension_detail_info.Description: Column proportions test (z-test).  Gives a different output for the column proportions test than the procedures "Crosstabs" and "Custom Tables". Output: row number, columns tested, z-values, p-values, the Bonferroni, Holm, Holland-Copenhaver and Benjamini-Hochberg adjustments for a given Alpha level. In a second table the test results are given. The  Alpha level is adjustable.
extension_detail_info.Author: Dr. Hans Grüner (http://gruener.userpage.fu-berlin.de)

extension_index.description: CWD - Current Working Directory.

extension_detail_info.Name: CWD
extension_detail_info.Summary: CWD - Current Working Directory.
extension_detail_info.Description: CWD - Current Working Directory. Extension command to emulate the old SPSS behavior that the current working directory (cwd) is equal to the syntax directory. In later SPSS versions, the cwd has become the spss installation directory, which is pretty useless IMHO.
extension_detail_info.Author: Albert-Jan Roskam

extension_index.description: Clean up correlation matrix

extension_detail_info.Name: FormatCorrelations
extension_detail_info.Summary: Clean up correlation matrix
extension_detail_info.Description: This procedure can improve the appearance of a correlation matrix in several ways.  It requires that the SPSSINC MODIFY TABLES extension command is installed.
extension_detail_info.Author: JKP, IBM SPSS

extension_index.description: Perform exact or fuzzy case-control matching.

extension_detail_info.Name: FUZZY
extension_detail_info.Summary: Perform exact or fuzzy case-control matching.
extension_detail_info.Description: This procedure matches cases and controls by utilizing random draws from the controls, based on a specified set of key variables. The command supports exact and fuzzy matching.  The input can be in a single dataset, or the cases and controls can be in different datasets.
extension_detail_info.Author: JKP, IBM SPSS

extension_index.description: Build a dataset of variable information from multiple dataset

extension_detail_info.Name: GATHERMD
extension_detail_info.Summary: Build a dataset of variable information from multiple datasets.
extension_detail_info.Description: This procedure builds a dataset containing the variable names, labels, and optionally selected custom variable attributes from one or more IBM SPSS Statistics, SAS, or Stata data files.
extension_detail_info.Author: JKP, IBM SPSS

extension_index.description: Open a data, syntax, or output file from a single dialog box

extension_detail_info.Name: generalopen
extension_detail_info.Summary: Open a data, syntax, or output file from a single dialog box
extension_detail_info.Description: This package provides a convenience dialog box that installs on the File menu and provides a unified way of opening a data, syntax, or output file without visiting submenus.  Data files can be sav or zsav.  A password can be supplied.
extension_detail_info.Author: JKP, IBM SPSS

extension_index.description: LSMON -  Monitor concurrent license usage

extension_detail_info.Name: LSMON
extension_detail_info.Summary: LSMON -  Monitor concurrent license usage
extension_detail_info.Description: LSMON -  Monitor concurrent license usage (as returned by lsmon.exe). Gives number and proportion of SPSS licenses used, by feature and by reserved/unreserved license type. This assumes that the caller has a concurrent license, and that the LSHOST environment variable points to the license server
extension_detail_info.Author: Albert-Jan Roskam

extension_index.description: Partial least squares regression

extension_detail_info.Name: PLS
extension_detail_info.Summary: Partial least squares regression
extension_detail_info.Description: This procedure estimates partial least squares (PLS, also known as "projection to latent structure") regression models. PLS is a predictive technique that is an alternative to ordinary least squares (OLS) regression, canonical correlation, or structural equation modeling, and it is particularly useful when predictor variables are highly correlated or when the number of predictors exceeds the number of cases.
extension_detail_info.Author: IBM SPSS JKP, JMB

extension_index.description: Produce confidence intervals for proportions

extension_detail_info.Name: PROPOR
extension_detail_info.Summary: Produce confidence intervals for proportions
extension_detail_info.Description: This procedure produces binomial and Poisson confidence intervals for proportions.  The binomial interval is based on the Jeffreys formula also used in error bar charts.
extension_detail_info.Author: JKP, IBM SPSS

extension_index.description: Propensity Score Matching

extension_detail_info.Name: PSM
extension_detail_info.Summary: Propensity Score Matching
extension_detail_info.Description: This dialog does propensity score matching for cases and controls.
extension_detail_info.Author: JKP IBM SPSS

extension_index.description: Quote SQL text appropriately for use in GET DATA

extension_detail_info.Name: STATS QUOTE SQLTEXT
extension_detail_info.Summary: Quote SQL text appropriately for use in GET DATA
extension_detail_info.Description: This package takes as input a file of SQL text that was not generated by the Database Wizard and add quotes as necessary for it to be used in the GET DATA command.  Wizard-generated text is already in this format, but SQL generated by an external tool or handwritten needs to be properly quoted before use.
extension_detail_info.Author: JKP, IBM SPSS

extension_index.description: R-based dialog for box plots from the box plot family

extension_detail_info.Name: RBoxplotFamily
extension_detail_info.Summary: R-based dialog for box plots from the box plot family
extension_detail_info.Description: Dialog to visualize the distribution of a scale variable by means of graphs of the box plot family: Highest Density Regions (HDR) Density Plot, Standard Box Plot, Violin Plot, Box-Percentile Plot and Highest Density Regions (HDR) Box Plot.
extension_detail_info.Author: Dr. Hans Grüner, Freie Universität Berlin
extension_detail_info.Categories: box_plot, dialog, dialog, extension_command, graphics, plots, r, spss, spssstatisticsextension, statistics

extension_index.description: Best subsets regression

extension_detail_info.Name: RegBestSubsets
extension_detail_info.Summary: Best subsets regression
extension_detail_info.Description: Dialog to get the best subsets for model building in a regression analysis, given a defined set of independent variables. The following statistics is computed: Mallows' Cp, R-Square, Adj. R-SQUARE, Std. Error of the Estimate, AIC and SBC.
extension_detail_info.Author: Dr. Hans Grüner, Freie Universität Berlin (http://gruener.userpage.fu-berlin.de)
extension_detail_info.Categories: best_subsets, dialog, extension_command, regression, spss, spssstatisticsextension, statistics

extension_index.description: Box-Cox Transformations

extension_detail_info.Name: RegBoxCoxTransforms
extension_detail_info.Summary: Box-Cox Transformations
extension_detail_info.Description: Dialog to check for a necessary transformation of the dependent in a regression analysis (Box-Cox Transformations)
extension_detail_info.Author: Dr. Hans Grüner, Freie Universität Berlin (http://gruener.userpage.fu-berlin.de)
extension_detail_info.Categories: box-cox, dialog, graphics, plots, regression, spss, statistics, transformations

extension_index.description: Component+Residual Plots (aka Partial Residual Plots)

extension_detail_info.Name: RegCompResPlots
extension_detail_info.Summary: Component+Residual Plots (aka Partial Residual Plots)
extension_detail_info.Description: Dialog to check for nonlinearity in the independents of a regression analysis.
extension_detail_info.Author: Dr. Hans Grüner, Freie Universität Berlin (http://gruener.userpage.fu-berlin.de)
extension_detail_info.Categories: component+resid​ual, dialog, graphics, linearity, nonlinearity, partial_residua​l, plots, regression, statistics

extension_index.description: R-based dialog for Mosaic and Association plots

extension_detail_info.Name: RMosaicAndAssociationPlots
extension_detail_info.Summary: R-based dialog for Mosaic and Association plots
extension_detail_info.Description: A dialog box interface for generating mosaic and association plots.
extension_detail_info.Author: Dr. Hans Grüner, Freie Universität Berlin
extension_detail_info.Categories: dialog, extension_command, graphics, plots, r, spss, residuals, statistics, spssstatisticsextension, tables

extension_index.description: Provides a large set of diagnostic plots and some tests for r

extension_detail_info.Name: RRegDiagGraph
extension_detail_info.Summary: Provides a large set of diagnostic plots and some tests for regresssion analysis (from Fox/Weisberg: An R Companion to Applied Regression, 2011)
extension_detail_info.Description: Plots and some tests for regresssion analysis: Residual's Density Plot , Residual's Q-Q Plot, Hat Values, Cook's Distance, Influence Plot, Residual Plots (also vs. the fitted values), Boxplots of Various Power Transformations, Box-Cox Transformation, Inverse Transformation Plot, Inverse Response Plot, Spread Level Plot, Added-Variable Plots, Leverage Plots, Component + Residual Plots, CERES Plots, Outlier Test, Breusch-Pagan Test, Box-Tidwell Transformations.
extension_detail_info.Author: Dr. Hans Grüner (http://gruener.userpage.fu-berlin.de)
extension_detail_info.Categories: dialog, graphics, r, spss, statistics, regression

extension_index.description: Regression diagnostic tests

extension_detail_info.Name: RRegDiagTest
extension_detail_info.Summary: Regression diagnostic tests
extension_detail_info.Description: This download provides a set of diagnostic tests for regresssion analysis (Harvey-Collier Test, Rainbow Test, RESET Test, Breusch-Pagan Test, Goldfeld-Quandt Test and Harrison-McCabe Test).
extension_detail_info.Author: Dr. Hans Grüner, Freie Universität Berlin (http://gruener​​.userpage.fu-b​e​rlin.de)
extension_detail_info.Categories: Breusch-Pagan, dialog, Goldfeld-Quandt​, graphics, Harrison-McCabe​, Harvey-Collier, plots, r, Rainbow, regression, RESET, statistics, tests

extension_index.description: Various methods for ridge regression and other approaches

extension_detail_info.Name: RRegRidge
extension_detail_info.Summary: Various methods for ridge regression and other approaches
extension_detail_info.Description: This extension command gives the opportunity to perform penalized (regularized) linear regressions. Methods are: 'classical' ridge regression, LASSO, LAR, Forward Stagewise, ridge regression (after Erika Cule) and elastic net.
extension_detail_info.Author: Dr. Hans Grüner, Freie Universität Berlin (http://gruener​​.userpage.fu-b​e​rlin.de)

extension_index.description: Extension command that can pass parameters to Python scripts

extension_detail_info.Name: SCRIPTEX
extension_detail_info.Summary: Extension command that can pass parameters to Python scripts
extension_detail_info.Description: This module provides a parameter passing mechanism for Python scripts run with the SCRIPT command via a PROGRAM and a mechanism for the script to return a value. The PROGRAM calls the runscript function with a parameter dictionary and script name. The script call the getscriptparams function to retrieve a parameter dictionary
extension_detail_info.Author: JKP, IBM SPSS

extension_index.description: Create syntax list from Variable Set definitions

extension_detail_info.Name: SETSMACRO
extension_detail_info.Summary: Create syntax list from Variable Set definitions
extension_detail_info.Description: This package pastes the definitions of one or more variable sets into a file so that the definitions can be used in syntax
extension_detail_info.Author: JKP, IBM SPSS

extension_index.description: Generate a new dataset from variable distributions in the act

extension_detail_info.Name: SimulateActiveDataset
extension_detail_info.Summary: Generate a new dataset from variable distributions in the active dataset
extension_detail_info.Description: This custom dialog generates a new dataset based on the active dataset.  Distributions are fit to the selected variables, including cross-variable correlation and contingency tables.  Values are then drawn randomly from these distributions.
extension_detail_info.Author: JKP, IBM SPSS

extension_index.description: Extended RECODE command

extension_detail_info.Name: SPSSINC RECODEEX
extension_detail_info.Summary: Extended RECODE command
extension_detail_info.Description: This command extends the built-in RECODE command in several ways. Date or time constants are used for variables of these types. Value labels can be automatically generated for the outputs.  Variable labels can be copied.  Variable types can be changed for the output variables.
extension_detail_info.Author: JKP, IBM SPSS

extension_index.description: Anonymize variables and data

extension_detail_info.Name: SPSSINC ANON
extension_detail_info.Summary: Anonymize variables and data
extension_detail_info.Description: This command replaces the values of the specified variables with new values according to one of three methods.  It is intended for situations where the true values must be concealed for privacy or other reasons.  It can also replace the variables names with anonymous equivalents.
extension_detail_info.Author: JKP, IBM SPSS

extension_index.description: Discover frequent itemsets, association rules using the Aprio

extension_detail_info.Name: SPSSINC APRIORI
extension_detail_info.Summary: Discover frequent itemsets, association rules using the Apriori algorithm
extension_detail_info.Description: The Apriori algorithm employs level-wise search to discover frequent itemsets and association rules within a dataset.  This procedure has been rewritten so as to depend only on the R plugin
extension_detail_info.Author: Jason Burke/Australia/IBM

extension_index.description: Perform TURF analysis

extension_detail_info.Name: SPSSINC TURF
extension_detail_info.Summary: Perform TURF analysis
extension_detail_info.Description: This procedure performs TURF analysis (Total Unduplicated Reach and Frequency), which finds groups of response variables that have the highest coverage in a sample. In contrast to simple frequencies, it accounts for the overlap in responses to different items.
extension_detail_info.Author: JKP, IBM SPSS

extension_index.description: Calculate standard and extended Rasch models

extension_detail_info.Name: STATS EXRASCH
extension_detail_info.Summary: Calculate standard and extended Rasch models
extension_detail_info.Description: This procedure calculates standard Rasch models and five extensions: RM: Binary Rasch, 0/1 item values, LLTM: Linear Logistic Test, 0/1 item values, RSM: Polytomous Rating Scale, more than two values, LRSM: Linear Rating Scale, more than two values, PCM: Polytomous Partial Credit, more than two values, and LPCM: Polytomous Linear Partial Credit, more than two values
extension_detail_info.Author: JKP, IBM SPSS

extension_index.description: Compute Fleiss Multi-Rater Kappa Statistics

extension_detail_info.Name: STATS FLEISS KAPPA
extension_detail_info.Summary: Compute Fleiss Multi-Rater Kappa Statistics
extension_detail_info.Description: Provides overall estimate of kappa, along with asymptotic standard error, Z statistic, significance or p value under the null hypothesis of chance agreement and confidence interval for kappa. Also provides similar statistics for individual categories.
extension_detail_info.Author: David Nichols, IBM SPSS

extension_index.description: Weighted Kappa Statistic Using Linear or Quadratic Weights

extension_detail_info.Name: STATS WEIGHTED KAPPA
extension_detail_info.Summary: 使用线性或二次权重的加权 kappa 统计
extension_detail_info.Description: 使用线性或二次权重以及置信区间和检验统计为两个评分者提供加权版本的科恩 Kappa。
extension_detail_info.Author: David Nichols, IBM SPSS

extension_index.description: Calculate Bayesian Analysis of Variance

extension_detail_info.Name: STATS BAYES ANOVA
extension_detail_info.Summary: Bayesian ANOVA
extension_detail_info.Description: This procedure performs a Bayesian analysis of variables.
extension_detail_info.Author: JKP, IBM SPSS

extension_index.description: Generate boxplots using R graphics.

extension_detail_info.Name: Rboxplot
extension_detail_info.Summary: Generate boxplots using R graphics.
extension_detail_info.Description: This procedure allows you to create boxplots from R with a variety of options. You can classify by one or more categorical variables, add notches, make the box widths proportional to the case count, scale the box widths, and choose box colors.
extension_detail_info.Author: IBM SPSS

extension_index.description: Calcuate Bayesian test of independence for two factors.

extension_detail_info.Name: STATS BAYES CROSSTABS
extension_detail_info.Summary: Calcuate Bayesian test of independence for two factors
extension_detail_info.Description: This procedure computes the Bayes factor testing independence for two factors in a crosstabulation framework.
extension_detail_info.Author: JKP, IBM SPSS

extension_index.description: Compute Bayesian regression models.

extension_detail_info.Name: STATS BAYES REGR
extension_detail_info.Summary: Compute Bayesian regression models
extension_detail_info.Description: This procedure calculates Bayes factors for sets of regression models and the posterior distribution.  Only continuous (scale level) variables can be used.
extension_detail_info.Author: JKP, IBM SPSS

extension_index.description: Bayesian T Test.

extension_detail_info.Name: STATS BAYES TTEST
extension_detail_info.Summary: Bayesian T Test
extension_detail_info.Description: This procedure calculates the Bayes factors and the posterior probabilities for a t test. The t test can be a one-sample test against a constant, an unpaired test, or a paired test. The posterior distributions for a single prior scale value can also be displayed.
extension_detail_info.Author: JKP, IBM SPSS

extension_index.description: C5.0 Decision Tree

extension_detail_info.Name: STATS C50 TREE
extension_detail_info.Summary: C5.0 Decision Tree
extension_detail_info.Description: This procedure estimates a classification tree model using the C5.0 algorithm. The output can be a tree or a set of rules. Missing data can be handled within the process. The procedure can also do predictions for the estimation data or a new dataset using a saved model. Boosting can be performed for increased accuracy.
extension_detail_info.Author: JKP, IBM SPSS

extension_index.description: Nonparametric regression.

extension_detail_info.Name: STATS_NONPAR_REGR
extension_detail_info.Summary: Nonparametric regression
extension_detail_info.Description: Nonparametric regression for continuous or categorical dependent variables
extension_detail_info.Author: JKP, IBM SPSS

extension_index.description: Open an SPSS file and apply a permanent dataset name to the r  esulting dataset.

extension_detail_info.Name: STATS GETSET DATASET
extension_detail_info.Summary: Open an SPSS file and apply a permanent dataset name to the resulting dataset
extension_detail_info.Description: This command provides a way to assign a permanent dataset name to an SPSS data file (.SAV or .ZSAV). That name can subsequently be applied to the session if the data file is opened using this command. The command provides two possible actions:  assign a permanent dataset name to be saved when the dataset is written to a file, and open a data file applying the permanent dataset name, if any, to it
extension_detail_info.Author: JKP, IBM SPSS

extension_index.description: Descriptive Statistics for a Population.

extension_detail_info.Name: STATS POPULATION DESCRIPTIVES
extension_detail_info.Summary: Descriptive Statistics for a Population
extension_detail_info.Description: Computes descriptive statistics assuming that data represent an entire population rather than a sample (uses N instead of N-1 in denominator to compute standard deviations and variances).
extension_detail_info.Author: David Nichols

extension_index.description: Quade nonparametric analysis of covariance.

extension_detail_info.Name: STATS QUADE ANCOVA
extension_detail_info.Summary: Quade nonparametric analysis of covariance
extension_detail_info.Description: Produces the Quade test of equality of conditional population distributions based on a rank analysis of covariance.
extension_detail_info.Author: David Nichols, IBM SPSS

extension_index.description: Pairwise Comparisons of Areas Under Independent ROC Curves.

extension_detail_info.Name: STATS ROC-COMPARE INDEPENDENT
extension_detail_info.Summary: Pairwise Comparisons of Areas Under Independent ROC Curves
extension_detail_info.Description: Provides comparisons of areas under independent ROC curves using methods from Hanley & McNeil (1982).
extension_detail_info.Author: David Nichols

extension_index.description: First Digit distribution of the selected variable graphed with the ideal Benford's Law distribution.

extension_detail_info.Name: Benfords_Law_Analysis
extension_detail_info.Summary: First Digit distribution of the selected variable graphed with the ideal Benford's Law distribution.
extension_detail_info.Description: This extension graphs the frequency distribution of the first numeric digit in a variable along with the ideal frequency distribution as defined by Benford's Law.  The analysis can accept only non-string variables, positive intergers greater or equal to 1.
extension_detail_info.Author: Doug Stauber

extension_index.description: Solves the traveling salesperson optimization problem

extension_detail_info.Name: Traveling Salesperson Problem
extension_detail_info.Summary: Solves the traveling salesperson optimization problem
extension_detail_info.Description: This extension uses the TSP package in R to solve the traveling salesperson optimization problem. The extension supports both symmetric and asymmetric costs (or distances).

extension_index.description: An example extension for automation test

extension_detail_info.Name: Descriptive Statistics Example
extension_detail_info.Summary: Example extension that runs Descriptives for scale variables and Frequencies for categorical variables
extension_detail_info.Description: This extension is primarily intended as a learning resource for users who are interested in building their own extensions. To view the source code and user interface design for this extension, launch the associated dialog from Extensions>Descriptive Statistics Example and then click Help.
extension_detail_info.Author: IBM SPSS

extension_index.description: Pairwise correlations with confidence intervals Description: This procedure computes pairwise correlations the same as   the built-in CORRELATIONS procedure but adds Fisher or bootstrap con  fidence intervals.

extension_detail_info.Name: STATS CORRELATIONS
extension_detail_info.Summary: Pairwise correlations with confidence intervals
extension_detail_info.Description: This procedure computes pairwise correlations the same as the built-in CORRELATIONS procedure but adds Fisher or bootstrap confidence intervals.
extension_detail_info.Author: JKP, IBM SPSS

extension_index.description: This procedure estimates a generalied additive model. GAM  s are linear in predictor terms that can be simple variables or vario  us kinds of splines or polynomials.  You can specify the error distri  bution and link function for the model.

extension_detail_info.Name: STATS GAM
extension_detail_info.Summary: Generalized Additive Model (GAM)
extension_detail_info.Description: This procedure estimates a generalied additive model. GAMs are linear in predictor terms that can be simple variables or various kinds of splines or polynomials.  You can specify the error distribution and link function for the model.
extension_detail_info.Author: JKP

extension_index.description: Create basis variables for various kinds of splines Description: This procedure creates a dataset of spline basis or ortho  gonal polynomial variables.  It can create polynomial splines, natura  l spllines, or orthogonal polynomials

extension_index.description: This extension provides a user interface for the SELECTPR  ED command. It takes a specified set of predictor variables as input and selects a smaller subset for use in predictive modeling procedures. A univariable method that considers each predictor in isolation is used, as opposed to the multivariable method of selecting predictors that is used by the Naive Bayes Classifier extension. The Select Predictors extension supports both categorical and scale dependent variables. Large sets of predictors can be handled.
